== English ==
=== Etymology ===
Its origins are not precisely known, though evidence suggests that it stems from a story of a traveller who arrives at an inn and loudly removes one of his shoes.  Then, realizing that others are sleeping, he removes his other shoe more carefully.  Some time later, a fellow traveller, rudely awakened and restless with anticipation, shouts, "Well, when are you gonna drop the other shoe!?"
